OL,3,CVaping, verbal abuse and truancy
OL,4,Cproblems found in many Welsh secondary
OL,5,Cschools
OL,7,FMost school leaders felt that the
OL,8,Foverall support from the Welsh
OL,9,FGovernment, local authorities and
OL,10,Fschool improvement services in dealing
OL,11,Fwith challenging behaviour is
OL,12,Finadequate. Schools were often
OL,13,Fproviding their own behavioural
OL,14,Fsupport provisions but too often did
OL,15,Fthis on a limited budget.
OL,17,FEstyn is recommending the national
OL,18,Fguidance on behaviour is updated, and
OL,19,Fa national campaign is launched by the
OL,20,FWelsh Government to try and improve
OL,21,Fbehaviour.
